                  <span class="badge-soft badge-critical">Critical</span> or
                  <span class="badge-soft badge-high">High</span> items, open
                  <strong>Runs &amp; Reports</strong> and triage them first.
                </p>
                <p style="margin-top:6px;">
                  <strong>2. Use "Top risk findings".</strong> This widget gives a
                  short list of findings that are most likely to break compliance or
                  production security. Each item links back to the exact file/line.
                </p>
                <p style="margin-top:6px;">
                  <strong>3. Use "Top noisy paths".</strong> Large numbers in
                  <span class="badge-soft badge-medium">Medium</span> or
                  <span class="badge-soft badge-low">Low</span> often come from
                  <code class="mono">tests/</code>, <code class="mono">examples/</code>
                  or generated code. You can safely deprioritise them after checking.
                </p>
                <p style="margin-top:6px;">
                  <strong>4. Export when done.</strong> In
                  <strong>Runs &amp; Reports</strong> you can export HTML/PDF and
                  attach them to Jira, Confluence or audit evidence for ISO 27001.
                </p>
