            <div class="overrides-table-wrapper">
              <div class="panel-header">
                <div class="panel-title">Override strategy</div>
                <div class="panel-subtitle">
                  Keep signal high while staying transparent
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="panel-body" style="font-size:11px;line-height:1.6;">
                <p>
                  The goal of rule overrides is to reduce <strong>noise</strong> while
                  keeping a full trail for audits. SECURITY_BUNDLE applies three
                  simple rules:
                </p>
                <ol style="margin-top:6px;margin-left:18px;">
                  <li>
                    <strong>Never delete evidence.</strong> Overrides mark findings as
                    ignored, but they still exist in
                    <span class="mono">findings_unified.json</span>.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Always document why.</strong> Each override has a short
                    reason so that future reviewers understand the context.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Review regularly.</strong> When the code base changes, or
                    when a new regulatory requirement is added, overrides should be
                    revisited.
                  </li>
                </ol>
                <p style="margin-top:6px;">
                  Use this tab as a quick view for both developers and auditors when
                  they want to know <em>why</em> certain findings do not appear in the
                  main dashboard.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>
